Let's expand the powers for $
\left(\blueD{3^3}\right)^{\greenD{2}}=\purpleD{n^6}$.

$\begin{align}
\left(\blueD{3^3}\right)^{\greenD2}&=\underbrace{\blueD{3^3\cdot 3^3}}_\greenD{\text{{2 times}}}
\\\\\\
&=\underbrace{
\underbrace{\blueD{3\cdot 3\cdot 3}}_\text{3 times}
\cdot \underbrace{\blueD{3\cdot 3\cdot 3}}_\text{3 times}}
_\greenD{\text{2 times}}
\\\\
&=\purpleD{\underbrace{n\cdot n\cdot n\cdot n\cdot  n\cdot  n }_\text{6 times}}
\\\\
\end{align}$

