$\begin{align}
\left(4^2\right)^{4}&=4^{2\cdot 4}
\\\\
&=4^8
\end{align}$

This follows from the general rule $\left(x^m\right)^{n}=x^{m\cdot n}$.

We can also see this is correct by expanding the powers.

$\begin{align}
\left(4^2\right)^{4}&=\underbrace{4^2\cdot 4^2\cdot 4^2\cdot 4^2}_\text{4 times}
\\\\\\
&=\underbrace{
\underbrace{4\cdot 4}_\text{2 times}
\cdot \underbrace{4\cdot 4}_\text{2 times}
\cdot \underbrace{4\cdot 4}_\text{2 times}
\cdot \underbrace{4\cdot 4}_\text{2 times}}
_\text{4 times}
\\\\
&=4^8
\end{align}$

